## 4. The Five-Layer Target Architecture

### Layer 1 — Foundation
- Drupal 10/11 (headless/hybrid)
- Structured content model, permissions, multisite
- GitOps fleet management (Kubernetes, ArgoCD, Terraform)
- Security baseline: CSP, RBAC, WAF, automated patching, audit logs
- CI/CD quality gates: visual regression, a11y, performance, OWASP

### Layer 2 — Design Tokens
- **Global Token Foundation:** Colour ramps, type scale, space, radii, motion
- **Semantic Tokens:** `color-action-primary`, `space-section-gap`, etc.
- **Multi-Brand Overlays:** Regional/campaign token sets with validated palettes
- **Style Dictionary Pipeline:** Figma Tokens → JSON → CSS custom properties → Drupal theme
- All sites derive from a single versioned token foundation

### Layer 3 — Component & Pattern
- **Drupal SDC Library:** 50–200+ audited components, each with Storybook stories
- **Machine-Readable Registry:** JSON schema per component describing purpose, slots, allowed styles, a11y metadata, token bindings
- **Page Pattern Store:** AI-generated layouts saved as reusable global templates, tagged by intent
- **Variant Engine:** Theme overrides within token bounds only

### Layer 4 — AI Orchestration
- **Prompt-to-Layout Engine:** LLM (Claude/GPT-4o) maps natural-language intent to components & tokens using the component registry as system context
- **Guardrailed Token Variator:** Mood-based style adjustments within predefined safe numeric ranges (e.g., hue ±15°, spacing ±0.25×)
- **Quality Pre-Flight:** axe-core, Pa11y, CSP scan, contrast check on every AI output before the editor sees it
- **Component Gap Detector:** Logs unmet intent → feeds quarterly component backlog

### Layer 5 — Experience
- **Conversational UI:** AI prompt panel, layout preview, refinement chat inside Drupal admin
- **Content Studio:** Decoupled editing with inline SEO, alt-text generation, inclusive-language checks
- **Self-Service Dashboard:** Site provisioning, token overrides, analytics

