## 5. Compatibility Layer (Critical Addition)

### Purpose
Bridge old and new systems during migration. This layer is temporary and is removed in the final state.

### Responsibilities

#### 5.1 Component Adapters
```json
{
  "legacy_component": "hero_old",
  "maps_to": "hero_sdc",
  "field_mapping": {
    "headline": "title",
    "image": "media",
    "cta_text": "call_to_action.label",
    "cta_url": "call_to_action.url"
  }
}
```

5.2 Content Transformers

· Normalize field structures across inconsistent content types
· Resolve duplicated or conflicting field definitions
· Map legacy Paragraph structures to new component configurations

5.3 Layout Interpreters

· Detect legacy layout configurations (Panels, Layout Builder old sections, Paragraphs)
· Convert to equivalent new-system Layout Builder or Experience Builder configs
· Flag unmappable layouts for manual migration

5.4 Hybrid Rendering Model

During migration, a single page may contain:

```
Page = Legacy Blocks + SDC Components
```

Requirements:

· Shared styling layer (design tokens)
· No visual drift between legacy and new components
· Unified CSS custom properties across both systems

