13. Conversational Site Builder — Interaction Model

The AI assistant lives inside the Drupal admin as a chat panel. Example interaction:

```
Editor: "I need a product launch page for our eco-friendly sneaker.
        Hero with looping video, three testimonial cards,
        a sustainability stats grid, and a newsletter sign-up.
        Vibrant, earthy, slightly edgy."

AI:     "Generated 3 layout options using only approved components
        and the brand's 'Evergreen' token set. All pass WCAG AA,
        mobile responsive, and security checks.

        Option A: Full-bleed hero, horizontal testimonials
        Option B: Split hero, stacked testimonials
        Option C: Editorial hero with image-lead

        Preview & refine →"

Editor: "I like Option B, but swap testimonials to the left
        and make the hero darker."

AI:     "Updated. Hero background shifted to token value 'surface-dark'.
        Testimonials moved to left column. All gates still passing.
        Ready to preview."
```

The AI cannot output raw CSS, unapproved markup, or external dependencies. Every proposal is validated by the pre-flight pipeline before the editor sees it.

