# Implementation Plan — Agentic Intent-to-Experience Platform

> Drupal-based enterprise WebCM migration from legacy to AI-augmented, token-driven platform. 5-phase rollout over 30 months with parallel coexistence, gradual adoption, and zero big-bang risk.

---

## 0. Migration Philosophy

- **No big-bang rewrite.** Systems coexist. Value is proven before legacy is decommissioned.
- **Parallel systems, gradual adoption.** New authoring becomes available; editors switch when ready.
- **Progress measured by component coverage, not site count.** A single page using new components is progress.
- **New system proves value before replacing old.** AI-assisted pages ship faster with higher quality — adoption follows naturally.

### Approach: Strangler Fig Pattern

```

Legacy Drupal → Hybrid → Component-driven → Fully Agentic

```

Incrementally replace:
1. **Styles → Tokens** first (lowest risk, highest immediate value)
2. **Components → SDC** second (builds the composable vocabulary)
3. **Layouts → Patterns** third (enables AI composition)
4. **Authoring → AI** last (depends on all prior layers)

---

## 1. Migration Strategy Overview

### Key Principle

> Migration succeeds when new content never uses legacy patterns again.

### Governance Rule

From Phase 2 onward: **all new pages must use SDC components and the token system.** Legacy authoring is locked for new content; it remains available only for editing existing pages.

---

## 2. Transition Phases (Full 30-Month Plan)

---

### Phase 0 — Discovery & Mapping
**Months 0–2 | Foundation**

#### Goals
- Understand current landscape
- Define migration scope and priorities
- Identify quick wins

#### Activities

**Component Audit**
- Inventory all Drupal themes, custom modules, and page templates across all sites
- Identify duplicates, near-duplicates, and dead code
- Select top 20 most-reused components for Phase 1 extraction

**Content Model Mapping**
- Map all content types across sites
- Identify field inconsistencies, duplicates, and diverged definitions
- Define target normalized schemas aligned with component props

**Template Analysis**
- Identify top 10 highest-traffic page templates
- Document layout patterns (landing page, product page, campaign page, article)
- These become the Phase 2 pattern migration priorities

**Stakeholder Interviews**
- Site editors: pain points, workflow friction, desired capabilities
- Brand teams: design drift concerns, approval bottlenecks
- Security: current posture, incident history, compliance requirements
- Platform/DevOps: infrastructure heterogeneity, deployment pain

#### Deliverables

| Deliverable | Description |
|-------------|-------------|
| Component Inventory | Full catalog with usage frequency, duplication score, technical debt rating |
| Content Model Map | All content types, fields, and interrelationships across sites |
| Migration Priority Matrix | Components and templates ranked by impact × migration effort |
| Stakeholder Report | Pain points, requirements, and success metrics by role |

---

### Phase 1 — System Foundation + Coexistence
**Months 1–6 | Build the New, Keep the Old**

#### Key Shift
New system exists alongside legacy. Both render production pages.

#### Activities

**Design Token Architecture**
- Establish three-tier token hierarchy: global → semantic → component
- Define in Figma Tokens / Style Dictionary
- Agree on naming conventions, brand sub-sets, regional override model
- Automate Figma ↔ code sync
- Map legacy styles to semantic tokens (the first bridge)

**Component Extraction (Top 20 → SDC)**
- Convert most-reused legacy Twig components to Drupal Single Directory Components (SDC)
- Normalize props, remove inline styles, bind to tokens
- Build Storybook stories with accessibility tests and visual regression snapshots
- Establish CI/CD pipeline for component validation and publishing

**Component Registry v1**
- Machine-readable JSON schema per component: name, description, slots, allowed fields, style variants, a11y metadata, token bindings
- Publish as API endpoint consumable by the AI layer

**Compatibility Layer**
- Build component adapters: legacy component → SDC field mappings
- Content transformers: normalize inconsistent field structures
- Layout interpreters (initial): detect legacy layouts, log for Phase 2 conversion

**Dual Rendering Support**
- Legacy pages continue rendering via existing theme
- New pages available via SDC components + token-mapped CSS
- Both systems share CSS custom properties from token layer — no visual drift

**Quality Gate Infrastructure**
- Deploy automated WCAG AA (axe-core + Pa11y), Core Web Vitals (Lighthouse CI), and OWASP ZAP scanning into deployment pipeline
- Define pass/fail thresholds
- Implement security headers, CSP policies, RBAC audit logging

**AI Content Copilot (Limited)**
- Integrate LLM into CKEditor for content generation, translation, summarization, and alt-text
- Mandatory human review on all AI-generated content
- No layout AI yet — content only

**Governance Cockpit v1**
- Central dashboard showing: component adoption rates, a11y scores, security posture per site

