| Deliverable | Details |
|-------------|---------|
| Design Token System | Versioned, published, consumed by all Drupal themes. Figma ↔ code sync automated. |
| SDC Library v1 | 20+ SDC components, Storybook stories, a11y + visual regression tested |
| Component Registry v1 | JSON API of component schemas, machine-readable |
| Compatibility Layer | Adapters, mappers, transformers for legacy ↔ new |
| CI/CD Quality Gates | WCAG AA, performance, security gates blocking deployment on failure |
| AI Content Copilot | Text, alt-text, SEO metadata in CKEditor |
| Governance Dashboard v1 | Adoption, a11y, security visibility per site |
| Security Baseline | CSP, RBAC, audit logs, automated patching pipeline |

---

### Phase 2 — Progressive Page Migration + AI Introduction
**Months 6–14 | New Pages → New System**

#### Key Shift
All new pages use SDC components and tokens. Old pages remain on legacy but are gradually converted.

#### Activities

**New Content Rule Enforcement**
- All new pages must use SDC components + token system
- Legacy Layout Builder disabled for new page creation
- Existing legacy pages remain editable in legacy mode

**Pattern-Based Migration**
- Convert top 10 highest-traffic templates into reusable page patterns
- Patterns are serialized Layout Builder / Experience Builder configs
- Patterns become few-shot examples for AI composition engine

**Assisted Migration Tools**
- Build scripts that detect legacy layouts and suggest equivalent new-system component patterns
- Semi-automated conversion for high-volume pages
- Manual migration workflow for edge cases

**Component Library Expansion**
- Expand SDC library from 20 → 50+ components
- Prioritize components needed for top page patterns
- All new components validated through CI quality gates

**AI Composition Engine (Internal Beta)**
- LLM prompted with component registry as system context
- Generates Layout Builder configs from natural language descriptions
- Internal testing only; editors see proposals but cannot publish AI layouts yet
- Component gap logging begins: capture "I wanted X but couldn't" signals

**Hybrid Rendering Maturation**
- Pages can render legacy blocks alongside SDC components
- Visual regression testing ensures no rendering differences
- Track hybrid page ratio as migration progress metric

**Editor Training**
- Train early-adopter site teams on new component system
- Document migration patterns and best practices
- Establish feedback loop for editor experience improvements

