### Phase 3 — Agentic Authoring Activation
**Months 12–20 | AI Becomes Primary Authoring Model**

#### Key Shift
Conversational AI authoring becomes the default for new content. Editors describe intent; AI assembles.

#### Activities

**Enable Full Agent Pipeline**
```

Intent (natural language)
→ Plan (AI selects components + patterns)
→ Compose (AI assembles Layout Builder config)
→ Validate (automated gates run)
→ Preview (editor reviews)
→ Publish

```

**AI Composition UI**
- Conversational chat panel inside Drupal admin
- AI returns 3–5 layout options using only approved components and brand tokens
- One-click preview, refine via subsequent prompts ("swap hero style", "make it darker")

**Token-Aware Style Variator**
- Mood-based token adjustments within safe, tested intervals
- "Make it more editorial" → adjusts spacing, typography, and color tokens
- Every adjustment auto-validated for contrast and accessibility

**Quality Pre-Flight Pipeline**
- Every AI-generated layout passes through full validation before editor sees it
- axe-core, Pa11y, CSP, contrast ratio, Core Web Vitals estimation
- Failed layouts never shown to editors

**Convert Patterns → AI Templates**
- Existing page patterns become few-shot examples for the LLM
- Patterns tagged by intent, audience, tone, and complexity
- AI learns from editor refinements: accepted layouts reinforce the model

**Editor Migration (Full Rollout)**
- All editors trained on conversational authoring
- Gradual transition: manual layout → AI-assisted → AI-first
- Fallback: editors can still manually assemble from components if AI suggestions don't fit

**Multi-Brand Tenant Model**
- AI is brand-context-aware: uses the requesting site's token overlay
- Regional token sets enforced; AI cannot cross-contaminate brands

**Component Evolution Loop Operational**
- Quarterly review of component gap logs
- DesignOps designs, validates, and ships new components
- Registry updated; AI immediately aware of new capabilities

