| Editor resistance to new authoring model | High | Gradual onboarding; keep legacy available for existing pages; prove time savings on new pages first |
| Inconsistent content models block normalization | Medium | Content transformers and adapters; accept some manual mapping for edge cases |
| Hybrid rendering creates visual drift | Medium | Shared token layer; automated visual regression testing; unified CSS custom properties |
| AI generates sub-optimal layouts | Medium | Human-in-the-loop; AI proposes, editors approve; feedback loop improves model |
| Security gaps during coexistence | High | Both systems pass through same CI/CD quality gates; no relaxation for legacy |
| Migration takes longer than planned | Medium | Phased rollout; value delivered incrementally; no big-bang dependency |

